NAME
    Dancer::Plugin::Res - Syntax sugar for setting the status and returning
    a response

VERSION
    version 0.0001

SYNOPSIS
        use Dancer;
        use Dancer::Plugin::Res;
        post '/widgets' => sub {
            return res 400 => 'Sorry, name param is required'
                unless param 'name';
        };
        dance;

DESCRIPTION
    This Dancer plugin provides the keyword "res()", which stand for
    response. Calling "return res 400, 'reason'" in a route is equivalent
    to:

        status 400;
        return 'reason';

